Certainly! The `quote-quotation` property can be designed to specify the style of quotation marks used for blockquotes or inline quotes. Here’s an example of how to define it in CSS:

```css
@supports (--css: variables) {
  :root {
    --quote-quotation: "“"; /* Default opening quote */
    --quote-quotation-close: "”"; /* Default closing quote */
  }

  blockquote {
    quotes: var(--quote-quotation) var(--quote-quotation-close);
  }

  blockquote::before {
    content: var(--quote-quotation);
  }

  blockquote::after {
    content: var(--quote-quotation-close);
  }
}
```

### Usage
You can then set the custom quote style using:

```css
.custom-quote {
  --quote-quotation: "‘"; /* Change opening quote */
  --quote-quotation-close: "’"; /* Change closing quote */
}
```

### Example HTML
```html
<blockquote class="custom-quote">
  This is a custom styled quote.
</blockquote>
```

### Note
This concept uses CSS variables to allow for easy customization and supports using different quotation styles as per user needs.

